700357f-b.title: Bronx: 233rd Street (East) - Webster Avenue
700357f-b.text:
(1)
East 233rd Street, east from Webster Ave., showing, on the north
side of the street, the Woodlawn station of the New York, New Haven
and Hartford Railroad. The street, at this point, sbans the railroad
tracks and the Bronx River.
June 6, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
Neg ~ 3e
(2)
An exclusive view of the New Haven Railroad's Woodlawn station.
It adjoins the N.E. corner of the Bronx River Parkway.
June 6, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
N2g NN 27

702062f-b.title: Bronx: Webster Avenue - 233rd Street (East)
702062f-b.text:
Webster Avenue, south of E. 233rd Street, showing in a set
of three views, street improvement operations being conducted
by the Works Progress Administration. On the left are the tracks
of the New York Central Railroad.
March 16, 1937
Views 1 and 2
View 31 September 22, 1937
W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
